                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
                <span class="rule-number">3</span>
                <div class="rule-content">
                    <h3>Context Pressure Changes Behavior</h3>
                    <p>At <strong>70% context usage</strong>, Claude starts losing precision. Run <code>/compact</code> at 70%, <code>/clear</code> at 90%. Monitor with <code>/status</code>.</p>
                    <div class="rule-metric">
                        <span class="metric-tag">70% = precision loss</span>
                        <span class="metric-tag">/compact at 70%</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
                <span class="rule-number">4</span>
                <div class="rule-content">
                    <h3>Start Simple, Scale Smart</h3>
                    <p>2-week test period before scaling. 4-phase adoption: solo tasks, multi-file work, agents, then CI/CD integration. Work through each phase, don't skip ahead.</p>
                    <div class="rule-metric">
                        <span class="metric-tag">2-week test period</span>
                        <span class="metric-tag">4-phase adoption</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="rule">
                <span class="rule-number">5</span>
                <div class="rule-content">
                    <h3>Methodologies Matter More with AI</h3>
                    <p>AI amplifies good code <strong>AND</strong> bad code. TDD for critical logic, SDD for architecture-first, BDD for PM/dev collaboration. Choose by context, not by habit.</p>
                    <div class="rule-metric">
                        <span class="metric-tag">TDD / SDD / BDD</span>
                        <span class="metric-tag">Choose by context</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
